%% Diagram: CDC variant of the transactional outbox
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Service
    participant DB as Postgres + WAL
    participant Deb as Debezium
    participant Reg as Registry
    participant K as Kafka

    App->>DB: BEGIN
    App->>DB: UPDATE orders SET status='PLACED'
    App->>DB: INSERT INTO outbox (...)
    App->>DB: COMMIT
    DB-->>Deb: stream WAL commit record
    Deb->>Reg: register / fetch schema
    Reg-->>Deb: schema id
    Deb->>K: publish(key=aggregate_id, schema-id + payload)
    K-->>Deb: ack
    Note over DB,K: Outbox row never re-read by polling.\nA separate TTL job purges processed rows.
